From: Yehonatan Cohen Scaly <scalys7@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 17:00:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] bwd-compat reconfig: new_from_dkg_output takes bwd-compat
 DKG output

A network reconfiguring under the bwd-compat Party always DKG'd under
the bwd-compat Party too — there's no flow where bwd-compat reconfig
consumes a post-bump main DKG output. The existing `new_from_dkg_output`
signature (`universal_public_output: decentralized_party::dkg::PublicOutput`)
forced callers to provide the wrong shape: bwd-compat DKG produces
`bwd_compat::dkg::PublicOutput`, a structural subset of the main type
(no trailing `threshold_encryption_to_sharing_output`), and there's no
`From` between them.

Fix: change the parameter to `super::dkg::PublicOutput`. The body only
reads legacy fields (every access exists on the bwd-compat shape), and
the inner `class_groups::reconfiguration::PublicInput::new` call uses
the existing `impl From<bwd_compat::dkg::PublicOutput> for
class_groups::dkg::PublicOutput` for its `dkg_output` arg.

Unblocks `crates/ika-core/src/dwallet_mpc/crytographic_computation/mpc_computations/reconfiguration.rs::reconfiguration_bwd_compat_public_input`'s
V2 arm in the ika `dev_backward_compatability` branch (PR #1710 in
`dwallet-network`).

Apply on top of 7795eb45 (current `main`):

    cd /path/to/cryptography-private
    git checkout main
    git checkout -b bwd-compat-reconfig-from-bwd-compat-dkg
    git am < /path/to/dwallet-network/docs/upstream-cryptography-private-bwd-compat-reconfig-from-bwd-compat-dkg.diff
    git push origin bwd-compat-reconfig-from-bwd-compat-dkg
---
 .../reconfiguration.rs                        | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/2pc-mpc/src/decentralized_party_backward_compatible/reconfiguration.rs b/2pc-mpc/src/decentralized_party_backward_compatible/reconfiguration.rs
--- a/2pc-mpc/src/decentralized_party_backward_compatible/reconfiguration.rs
+++ b/2pc-mpc/src/decentralized_party_backward_compatible/reconfiguration.rs
@@ -197,7 +197,7 @@ impl PublicInput {
             ); MAX_PRIMES],
         >,
         current_tangible_party_id_to_upcoming: HashMap<PartyID, Option<PartyID>>,
-        universal_public_output: decentralized_party::dkg::PublicOutput,
+        universal_public_output: super::dkg::PublicOutput,
     ) -> crate::Result<Self> {
         let ristretto_setup_parameters =
             RistrettoSetupParameters::derive_from_plaintext_parameters::<ristretto::Scalar>(
